    {
      "text": "Which of the following statements regarding polio surveillance indicators is correct? At least 80% of expected routine AFP surveillance reports should be received on time, including zero reports where no AFP cases are seen. The sensitivity of surveillance requires detecting at least two cases of non-polio AFP annually per 100,000 population aged less than 15 years in endemic regions. Completeness of case investigation mandates that all AFP cases must have three stool specimens collected within 7 days of paralysis onset. Laboratory performance standards dictate that AFP case specimens must be processed in any accredited clinical laboratory within the country.",
      "options": [
        {
